Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Up 
Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange National-100 Index closed at 5,930.82
points on Friday, up 211.92 points, or 3.68 percent, from Thursday's
finish.
The trading was heavy with the turnover reaching over 157 trillion
Turkish Liras (over 335 million U.S. dollars).
The financial index rose 313.27 points, or 4.22 percent, to close at
7,696.18 points, the industrial index increased 110.67 points, or 2.59
percent, to close at 4,356.91 points and the services index went up
102.11 points, or 1.59 percent, to close at 6,527.75 points.
